message.reasoning_content:
The user is asking me to respond to a survey about AI in education. I need to provide responses for each of the 10 statements (TT4G35A through TT4G35J) using one of the five response options: "Strongly disagree", "Disagree", "Agree", "Strongly agree", or "I don't know".

As a teacher responding to these statements, I should provide thoughtful responses based on realistic classroom perspectives. Let me think through each statement:

TT4G35A: AI helps write/improve lesson plans - This is reasonable. Many teachers find AI tools helpful for brainstorming and drafting lesson materials. AGREE

TT4G35B: AI enables adapting materials to different abilities - AI can personalize content. This is a capability AI systems have. AGREE

TT4G35C: AI assists in supporting students individually - AI can provide personalized learning experiences. AGREE

TT4G35D: AI supports students with specific needs - AI can help with accessibility features, translation, etc. AGREE

TT4G35E: AI helps automate administrative tasks - Definitely true. STRONGLY AGREE

TT4G35F: AI enables misrepresenting others' work - This is about the risk/concern that students can use AI to plagiarize. This is a real concern. AGREE

TT4G35G: AI makes inappropriate/incorrect recommendations - This is a valid concern about AI reliability. AGREE

TT4G35H: AI amplifies biases - This is a documented concern about AI systems. AGREE

TT4G35I: AI jeopardizes privacy/security - Valid data privacy concerns. AGREE

TT4G35J: AI suggests unsuitable pedagogical approaches - This is a concern about AI recommendations not aligning with best teaching practices. AGREE

I'll provide these responses in a balanced way that reflects both the benefits and concerns of AI in education.
